  "title": "Security Officer - In house",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Overview:</strong></p>\n<p>We are seeking a reliable and responsible Security Officer to join our team and ensure the safety and security of our premises, assets, and personnel. As a Security Officer, you will be expected to maintain a visible presence, conduct regular patrols, monitor surveillance systems, and respond to incidents promptly.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>* Monitor and patrol assigned areas to detect and respond to potential security risks.</p>\n<p>* Control access to the premises by checking IDs, issuing visitor passes, and ensuring proper authorization.</p>\n<p>* Observe and report suspicious activity to management and authorities as necessary.</p>\n<p>* Operate and monitor security systems, including surveillance cameras and alarm systems.</p>\n<p>* Enforce safety protocols and company policies to maintain a secure environment.</p>\n<p>* Respond promptly to emergency situations, accidents, or alarms and provide appropriate action.</p>\n<p>* Prepare incident reports and logs for daily activities.</p>\n<p>* Assist in crowd control and manage access during events, as needed.</p>\n<p>* Work with law enforcement and emergency services when necessary.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<p>* Valid security certification (e.g., PLRD, RTT, etc.) is required.</p>\n<p>* Experience in condo or serviced apartment industry required.</p>\n<p>* Proven experience in security or a related field (preferred, but not mandatory).</p>\n<p>* Strong attention to detail and ability to remain alert during long shifts.</p>\n<p>* Ability to respond quickly and effectively in emergency situations.</p>\n<p>* Must be physically fit and capable of handling the demands of the role.</p>\n<p>* Ability to work flexible hours, including nights, weekends, and holidays.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\n<p>* Competitive salary</p>\n<p>* Health and wellness benefits</p>\n<p>* Opportunities for career advancement</p>\n<p>* Paid training and certification</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Working Hours and Timing:</strong></p>\n<p>• Shift Pattern: [12-hour shifts , rotating schedule]</p>\n<p>• Working Hours: [4 days of work followed by 2 days off in a rotating schedule]</p>\n<p>• On-call availability may be required in case of emergencies.</p>\n<p>Note: The security officer will be expected to work in shifts, and the schedule may vary based on the organization's operational needs.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Working Location:</strong></p>\n<p>2 Teck Chye Terrace Singapore 545726</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>How to Apply:</strong></p>\n<p>Interested candidates can send resumes and cover letters to Ms. Kimberly Teoh, email address : kimberly.teoh@gh15group.com</p>",
